Package: xtop
Version: 0.47.2-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 37740
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.47.2 polishes the PHP-FPM diagnostic with output fixes + a
 false-positive eliminator for the docroot web-shell scanner.
 .
 Output improvements:
   - MASTERS table now properly aligned columns (PHP / POOL /
     WORKERS / LISTEN / STATE) instead of wide one-line entries.
   - "STATUS-FAIL" is gone for pools without pm.status_path. New
     state "no-status" (dim) means the pool is healthy but not
     introspectable — the Plesk + manual-setup default. Genuine
     failures show as "no-socket" or "unreachable" (red).
 .
 False-positive fixes for filesystem web-shell scan:
   - `create_function` needle now requires the open-paren — bare
     string mentions (in security-validator deny-lists) no longer
     trigger.
   - Files in `*validator*`, `*sanitiz*`, `*/security/*`, `*firewall*`
     paths are skipped.
   - Files containing `$forbidden`, `$blacklist`, `$denylist`,
     `$banned_functions`, `$dangerous_functions`, `$disabled_functions`,
     or classes named `Validator`/`Sanitizer`/`Firewall`/`SecurityCheck`
     in their head bytes are treated as defensive code and skipped.
 .
 Verified zero false positives on 22-site Plesk + 18-site aaPanel
 with --deep-scan forced. All v0.47.1 multi-pool / Plesk / cPanel
 features remain intact.
